  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "IT Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Provide end-user IT support with priority handling for VIP users</p></li><li><p>Troubleshoot hardware, software, networking, and M365 issues (including remote support)</p></li><li><p>Perform device onboarding/offboarding, handover/collection, and basic IT asset management</p></li><li><p>Handle call logging, ticket tracking, and SLA response via ITSM tools</p></li><li><p>Set up and configure laptops/desktops; create/manage AD user profiles</p></li><li><p>Coordinate vendor repairs and manage DaaS device incidents</p></li><li><p>Support mobile device management (preferably Intune) and video/audio conferencing</p></li><li><p>Assist with BAU activities such as hardware refresh and Windows upgrades</p></li><li><p>Prepare and update basic technical documentation</p></li><li><p>Provide backend server/backup troubleshooting support (added advantage)</p></li><li><p>Mailbox management experience is an advantage<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><p>Around 3 years of Desktop/End-User Support experience</p></li><li><p>Good communication skills</p></li><li><p>Positive and proactive attitude</p></li><li><p>Diploma holder</p></li></ul>",
